If I end up getting COVID-19, it will be from visiting this restaurant.  We called to order a meal to pick-up, and were told it would be ready in 15 minutes. We arrive at Mickey’s 15 minutes later. While employees are wearing masks, none of the guests are and there is no social distancing enforced. On its own, that’s fine. While I wouldn’t choose to sit and eat in a restaurant in the current environment, legally they’re not doing anything wrong.  So in and out, grab our food, no problem, right?  Wrong.  The problem is that we had to wait an additional 20 minutes once we were inside the restaurant (after first being ignored for 10 minutes and then told there was a delay in our order). So instead of being a safe, in and out trip, we had to stand around in a potentially dangerous environment waiting for our food. I regret not leaving sooner.  The food itself was fine, but not good enough to warrant the possible exposure to COVID-19.  In conclusion, if you’re not worried or don’t care about the pandemic, then this is a fine place to eat. However if you are high-risk (like myself) or someone who is trying to be even a little bit cautious, avoid this restaurant and DO NOT order takeout.
